    "body": "Would need much more data to claim significant performance differences between bare metal and docker performance. In theory bare metal must be >= docker, unless some issue with compiled native dependencies. If that's the case we should benchmark how blst-ts pre-builds performs in different enviornments, instead of measuring overall performance which can be affected by many other variables.\r\n\r\nClosing for now, if relevant the issue should be continued as \"blst-ts pre-build performance across environments\"",
